-- Apax Partners May Buy German Retailer Takko for $1.71 Billion, WSJ Reports
-- B y   P e t e r   J .   B r e n n a n
-- 2010-12-20T17:19:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-20/apax-partners-may-buy-german-retailer-takko-for-1-71-billion-wsj-reports.html
Apax Partners LLP may acquire Takko,
a German retailer, for 1.3 billion euros ($1.71 billion), the
Wall Street Journal said, citing unidentified people familiar
with the matter.  A deal by Dec. 23 is likely for Takko, which is owned by
Advent International Corp., the Journal said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter J. Brennan at 
 pbrennan3@bloomberg.net  